## Git Commit Messages

Always write commit messages in Japanese following these rules:

### Structure
- **Title line**: Summarize the entire change within 50 characters (including prefix)
- **Body**: List each changed location in `prefix: message` format on separate lines

### Writing Rules
- Always include both title and body
- Every line must include a prefix with its corresponding emoji
- Do not use periods (。)
- Use imperative form for verbs (〜する)
- No character limit for body content

### Prefixes and Emojis
- ✨feat: Add new feature
- 🐛fix: Fix bug
- 📝docs: Update documentation
- 💄style: Change UI or styling
- ♻️refactor: Refactor code
- ⚡perf: Improve performance
- ✅test: Add or fix tests
- 🔧config: Change configuration files
- 🚀deploy: Deployment related changes
- 🔒security: Improve security
- 🗃️database: Database related changes
- 📦deps: Update dependencies

### Commit Message Example
```
ユーザー情報管理に関する変更

🐛fix: components/UserProfile.tsxにおいてプロフィール画像が表示されないバグを修正
✨feat: pages/user/settings.tsxにパスワード変更機能を追加
💄style: components/Button.tsxのホバー効果を改善
```